## What I Am Still Thinking About

Something I am sitting with after today: in a real organization, who actually owns the connection between these three pillars? In a large enterprise there might be a dedicated GRC team that sits across all three. But in a smaller organization — or a resource-constrained healthcare environment — governance might sit with IT leadership, risk might live with the security team, and compliance might be owned by legal or HR.

How do you make sure those groups are actually talking to each other? How do you stop them from operating in silos even when the intent is to be integrated? I do not have a clear answer yet. But I think the organizations that figure this out are the ones that end up with genuinely resilient security programs — and the ones that do not are the ones that end up in breach reports.

